title.narrative: SPA- Cost Reimbursable Contract: Development Outreach and Communication (DOC) Support to KEA

description.narrative: (Kenya): .Development Outreach and Communication (DOC) Support activity provides the Mission with a wide range of communications and outreach services. In Kenya, the activity is contributing to the mission's overarching communications objective: to increase strategic engagement with KEA target audiences in support of Kenya's Journey to Self-Reliance (J2SR). ..DOC plays a key role in developing and implementing USAID KEA's multi-year communications strategy. The results-based approach aims to engage and empower staff and implementing partners, increase the number of Kenyan voices engaged in a national dialogue on development and the use of evidence and data in communications-related decision making. The activity infuses a private sector lens on development and organizational communications practices and often partners with Kenyan firms' private sector to research or deliver compelling messages to local communities. DOC creates relevant, impactful, and high-quality visual and written content that highlight the U.S. tax payers dollars that produce real-life impact in the lives of Kenyans. .The importance of DOC's activities include effective communications and outreach, delivering information to audiences. As a result, it builds greater understanding of USAID's investments, and ensure that local voices and perspectives inform development programs and their objectives. The project contributes to the mission's overarching communications objective to increase strategic engagement with key target audiences in support of Kenya's Journey to Self-Reliance (J2SR) and the Mission's development objectives through focused, targeted communications and outreach.
